 Microsoft continues to invest in and serve the U.S. Government (USG) through Microsoft Federal. Microsoft Federal delivers a single unified organization centered around our customer: All critical customer functions are brought under the same organizational umbrella. Microsoft Federal offers our full spectrum of products and services, including hardware, software, online products, and consulting and services, bringing together the breadth and depth in our space with a razor sharp focus on serving the U.S. Government. 
Are you passionate about using technology to solve some of the toughest problems facing the organizations? Do you value the deployment of solutions into production with real world impact? Are you obsessive about the quality and consistency of the work you do in leading teams to deliver value and meeting the mission of our customers? 
If so, the Project Manager position at the Microsoft is for you! 
This role will be part of Microsoftâ€™s US Delivery Center (USDC), located in Las Colinas, Texas. The USDC is focused on bringing our industrialized consulting services to US Public Sector and Commercial customers in regulated industries, with stringent data security and US citizenship requirements. Our goal is to help our customers transition to cloud in a cost effective and scalable manner. 
Job Description: 
Part leader, part mentor, and part consultant, our team of Project Managers comprises an unusual mix of project management and consulting skills, along with a passion for technology. We are responsible for keeping the project team working on the highest priority tasks, removing risks and impediments, and leading the communication with the end customer. 
In this role, you will be responsible for providing support in the areas of project financials, resourcing, status reporting, and helping to identify, pursue, and close project risks and issues. You must have the ability to foster relationships with project teams, demonstrate value through service delivery, and improve service levels for our customer, all within the constraints of schedule, budget, and resources.
 Responsibilities 
You will have the responsibility of providing support for overall delivery and execution of the project working across multiple business teams. You will work in tandem with project managers specializing in different solution areas (Azure Cloud and Artificial Intelligence, Modern Work, and Business Applications). 
Areas of responsibility include: Financial Management â€“ management of planned hours, actuals, estimate to complete, estimate at completion, overall cost, revenue, budget, and management of financial variance. Risk Management â€“ managing and ensuring all potential risks and issues are properly communicated and mitigated. Status Updates â€“ develop status reports to stakeholders and update internal tools with project status details.
 Qualifications 
